parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as the vehicle surges forward unexpectedly.
symptoms: The engine "revs" while stopped at a stop sign or stop light
the car accelerates by itself without applying the accelerator
the car jolts forward unexpectedly
the engine idles high and lunges forward
the vehicle surges while in gear but at a stop
the vehicle suddenly races to a high idle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to accidents and injuries.

fuel lines leak gas.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Difficulty starting the vehicle can lead to inconvenience, frustration, and potentially strand the driver.

especially in damp weather
despite replacing spark plugs and battery.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A rusted frame can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to safety concerns.
symptoms: The frame of the car is nearly rusted away.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to lock up or fail to release, potentially leading to injuries or trapping the driver or passenger in the vehicle.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor locks up

the seat belt buckle gets stuck in the locked position
the seat belt does not lock into the buckle
the seat belt does not lock up during an accident.

rust in the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to honor recall notices can lead to unsafe vehicles on the road, putting drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Dealership unwilling to repair or replace recalled parts
statute of limitations cited as reason for not fixing recall item.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electronic Fuel Injection Control Unit Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the electronic fuel injection control unit can cause engine problems, stalling, or failure to start.
symptoms: Electronic fuel injection control unit failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the igniter can cause fuel to be dumped into the exhaust system, leading to fires or engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer and mileage indicator can cause the driver to be unaware of their speed and mileage, leading to potential safety risks.
